<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-15T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="1141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1141">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/64.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Miller</persName>.</hi><note n="97" xml:id="d1141fn97">Same to the American Consul at Durango except
                                changing words “local authorities “to “Carranza.”</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-15T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 15, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>State to local authorities that Department is informed that some American
                            citizens who have been forced by recent disturbed conditions to leave
                            vicinity of Tampico own leases on property that vicinity on which
                            rentals are coming due very soon which cannot be paid now because of
                            conditions prevailing and that it is expected that the authorities will
                            perceive the justice of taking no action in forfeiture of leases until
                            owners have had reasonable time to pay rent.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>